  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting sustainable development of stone industry in Iran</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Iranian stone industry faces the challenges associated with the access to external markets and take opportunity of the new markets. This, in turn, requires respective upgrading of the existing human and technical capacities to facilitate increased competitiveness of the Iranian produce at the regional and international markets. In this context, the Government of Iran requested UNIDO to propose technical cooperation project aimed to contribute to the Government#s efforts for implementation and achievement of the goals of the 20-year vision and the sixth 5-Year National Development Plan for the 2016-2021 through industrial upgrading and modernization of the stone industry of Iran.  The expected results of the proposed UNIDO project are:  - modernization of the pilot beneficiary pilot industrial enterprises operating in the stone industry of Iran that form networks, aimed to expand and diversify their production, improve productive performance and material and energy efficiency, human resource and financial management, marketing practices that facilitates better access to regional and international markets; increased value added from the local, regional and international operations of the project beneficiary pilot enterprises; - enhanced export capacities and stronger linkages across the stone processing value cha</narrative>
  </description>
